text: Food is decent but not as good as before. Black carrot cake burnt, chicken wings bland, maggie goreng bland, bbq lala salty.

This Hawker is close to Botanical Garden. Foods are cheap for only $4-6 and yummy. Some accepts Online payment, some just cash!

They have wall fans all over so very comfortable to eat.

Hawker food atmosphere. So queue, collect and return your food and trays.
Still lots of memories here. Good to see it being retained and serving the public.
A bit expensive for teh halia $2.
Bit late at night (10pm) so most stalls closed. Great mee goreng though on my first food in Singaoore for 18 months

Drove here after a workout at MacRitchie Reservoir. Order from the famous Selera Rasa Nasi Lemak stall recommended by a friend.

The rice is fragrant and has a good texture. The fried chicken wings and egg were freshly made.

Will be coming back to try the other famous stalls/dishes like mee soto, indian rojak and prawn noodles.
